label: Australian physiographic units
description:
A list of physiographic units in Australia that provide a consistent framework for mapping soils and landforms at national and regional scales, compiled at a continental scale. The list was defined by Pain et al. (2011; https://www.clw.csiro.au/aclep/documents/PhysiographicRegions_2011.pdf)* and built on the work of Jennings and Mabbutt (1986). It recognises a subdivision of the Australian onshore continent into three physiographic divisions, 23 physiographic provinces and 220 physiographic regions. The three divisions correspond broadly with the geological subdivision into the western shields, the central basins and the eastern fold belts. Provinces can be used to make interpretations about landscape processes at the broadest scale; descriptors for provinces include a name, geology, structure, and broad regolith types. The primary descriptors for regions are geographic name and a simple text description including major geologic and geomorphic features. Bounding box coordinates in decimal degrees are included. Each physiographic unit is also identified by a numeric code (one, three, and five digits for divisions, provinces and regions, respectively). For physiographic units within Western Australia, notations provided include extensions to five-digit numbering for divisions and provinces, to allow better characterization for database purposes. For Western Australian physiographic units, an alphabetical code is also listed; these consist of three upper-case letters for the division and provinces, with an additional two lower-case letter suffix for regions. These alphabetical codes are used by the Geological Survey of Western Australia (GSWA) to spatially assign regolith units to the correct physiographic unit during mapping. GSWA describes a physiographic unit as 'A named geomorphological entity with internal coherence in its landform characteristics and landform evolutionary history. At the lowest levels, physiographic units reflect the underlying geology and have similar groupings of regolith materials that are related to the landform types, their evolution, and the underlying bedrock.'
*Pain, C, Gregory, L, Wilson, P and McKenzie, N (2011), The physiographic regions of Australia – Explanatory notes 2011; Australian Collaborative Land Evaluation Program and National Committee on Soil and Terrain (dataset available at https://www.asris.csiro.au/themes/PhysioRegions.html).

concepts.label: Albany Esperance Sandplain
concepts.definition: Sandplains with weakly to moderately incised southerly valley and intervening hills and low ranges of granite and metamorphic rocks (extending as headlands and inlets). Bounded by latitudes 33.228449°S and 35.193981°S, and longitudes 117.406742°E and 123.719394°E.

concepts.label: Alberga Dunefield
concepts.definition: Longitudinal dunes. Bounded by latitudes 26.565983°S and 27.346617°S, and longitudes 133.992033°E and 135.275623°E.

concepts.label: Alice Tableland
concepts.definition: Perched sandy plain with interior drainage and higher ferruginous-capped rim. Bounded by latitudes 20.445512°S and 23.550995°S, and longitudes 144.35352°E and 146.446376°E.

concepts.label: Amadeus Plains
concepts.definition: Dunefields and sandplains with scattered sandstone ranges; salt lakes and calcrete plains along lowland axis. Bounded by latitudes 22.709191°S and 26.220225°S, and longitudes 127.27787°E and 134.800216°E.

concepts.label: Andamooka Tableland
concepts.definition: Dissected sandstone plateau with bold east escarpment. Bounded by latitudes 30.687442°S and 33.439282°S, and longitudes 137.203797°E and 137.843292°E.

concepts.label: Anketell Hills
concepts.definition: Low mesas, buttes and stony rises of lateritized sandstone and shale among east–west longitudinal dunes and sandy plains. Bounded by latitudes 19.996901°S and 21.445172°S, and longitudes 121.516735°E and 124.333161°E.

concepts.label: Armraynald Plain
concepts.definition: Clay floodplain. Bounded by latitudes 17.470579°S and 20.148752°S, and longitudes 138.439832°E and 140.267239°E.

concepts.label: Arnhem Plateau
concepts.definition: Dissected sandstone plateau. Bounded by latitudes 11.898184°S and 14.617665°S, and longitudes 132.164189°E and 135.636903°E.

concepts.label: Arnhem Ridges
concepts.definition: Ranges of folded metamorphic rocks extending north–east as islands. Bounded by latitudes 12.459513°S and 14.451428°S, and longitudes 135.057019°E and 135.759996°E.

concepts.label: Atherton Tableland
concepts.definition: Basaltic tableland. Bounded by latitudes 17.133515°S and 17.744619°S, and longitudes 145.307072°E and 145.897773°E.

concepts.label: Augustus Ranges
concepts.definition: Parallel ranges and dissected plateaus with intervening hardpan wash plains and stony plains. Bounded by latitudes 21.366927°S and 25.861701°S, and longitudes 114.943213°E and 120.791266°E.

concepts.label: Australian Alps
concepts.definition: Dissected high upland, glaciated locally with some periglacial features. Uplifted blocks surrounded by highly dissected high relief hill country. Bounded by latitudes 34.726109°S and 36.855898°S, and longitudes 147.086632°E and 149.207529°E.

concepts.label: Avon Plateau
concepts.definition: Gently undulating surface of sandplains and ferruginous divides; stripped granitic slopes; and broad valley floors with salt lake chains. Bounded by latitudes 29.477967°S and 33.961952°S, and longitudes 115.854588°E and 120.972928°E.

concepts.label: Barkly Tablelands
concepts.definition: Black clay plains, sandy rises of ferruginous sandstone, and minor stony limestone plains, interior drainage with calcrete in depressions. Bounded by latitudes 16.685914°S and 22.513587°S, and longitudes 133.034327°E and 139.341168°E.

concepts.label: Barkly–Tanami Plains Province
concepts.definition: Uplands and interior lowlands with a northwest–southeast trend parallel to and including coastal lowlands, dominated by the Fitzroy River catchment. Bounded by latitudes 14.222438°S and 23.423680°S, and longitudes 127.703369°E and 139.516732°E.

concepts.label: Birrundudu Plain
concepts.definition: Low basaltic and sedimentary plain with clay soils and lateritic areas; indeterminate drainage with large claypans. Bounded by latitudes 16.91233°S and 18.846902°S, and longitudes 127.703369°E and 130.556829°E.

concepts.label: Davenport Ranges
concepts.definition: Fold belt of bevelled sandstone ridges, with narrow lowlands on weaker rocks; central tract of lower hills and plains; extensive ferruginous mantles. Bounded by latitudes 17.255769°S and 21.751149°S, and longitudes 133.415927°E and 135.896353°E.

concepts.label: Sandover Sandplain
concepts.definition: Sandplain with minor low sandstone tablelands and floodouts; sandy ferruginous plains in south. Bounded by latitudes 17.692407°S and 22.399285°S, and longitudes 133.681662°E and 137.472613°E.

concepts.label: Sturt Plateau
concepts.definition: Shallowly dissected plateau of ferruginized sandstone with alluviated valleys. Bounded by latitudes 14.222438°S and 17.956062°S, and longitudes 131.590314°E and 137.65821°E.

concepts.label: Tanami Sandplain
concepts.definition: Sandplain with minor longitudinal dunes in south; floodplains and floodouts on margins; stony rises in north. Bounded by latitudes 16.374853°S and 22.820198°S, and longitudes 127.727898°E and 134.708285°E.

concepts.label: Tanami Sandplain and Ranges
concepts.definition: Sandplain with scattered low ranges and tablelands and occasional granitic and sedimentary hills. Bounded by latitudes 17.932231°S and 20.656264°S, and longitudes 127.730425°E and 130.59688°E.

concepts.label: Tobermory Plain
concepts.definition: Slightly dissected limestone plain, part stony and part sandy. Bounded by latitudes 21.199697°S and 23.253064°S, and longitudes 135.675156°E and 139.516732°E.

concepts.label: Toko Plateaus
concepts.definition: Dissected sandstone plateaus. Bounded by latitudes 22.389649°S and 23.42368°S, and longitudes 136.724119°E and 138.561994°E.

concepts.label: Barrier Ranges
concepts.definition: Ranges and undulating lowlands of granite and metamorphics. Bounded by latitudes 30.590752°S and 32.635232°S, and longitudes 140.543994°E and 142.13811°E.

concepts.label: Bass Coastal Platforms
concepts.definition: Low coastal platforms, partly dune covered, with some mudstone and metamorphic hills. Bounded by latitudes 40.371399°S and 42.232601°S, and longitudes 144.322128°E and 148.349213°E.

concepts.label: Bass Islands
concepts.definition: Islands with low plateaus, partly dune covered with granite residual hills. Bounded by latitudes 39.435318°S and 40.594002°S, and longitudes 143.819443°E and 148.498795°E.

concepts.label: Bathurst Tablelands
concepts.definition: Granitic and basaltic tablelands and minor lowlands; includes the Canobolas dissected volcanic pile. Bounded by latitudes 32.281111°S and 34.94012°S, and longitudes 148.688503°E and 150.322949°E.

concepts.label: Belyando Plains
concepts.definition: Clay plains and sandy plains with minor hills. Bounded by latitudes 21.111979°S and 23.889474°S, and longitudes 148.082155°E and 146.173549°E.

concepts.label: Boulia Downs
concepts.definition: Undulating clay plains with minor stony limestone plains. Bounded by latitudes 21.944785°S and 23.067808°S, and longitudes 138.884884°E and 140.03994°E.

concepts.label: Broadsound Plains
concepts.definition: Plains, mainly alluvial, locally stony, with tidal flats. Bounded by latitudes 22.104335°S and 24.406156°S, and longitudes 151.600625°E and 149.366618°E.

concepts.label: Buckland Plateau
concepts.definition: Dissected high plateau on basalt and sandstone. Bounded by latitudes 24.454735°S and 25.155273°S, and longitudes 147.608298°E and 147.608298°148.368858°E.

concepts.label: Bulgonunna Tableland
concepts.definition: Undulating tableland; higher centre and sloping margins on volcanic rocks with peripheral mantle of ferruginous clayey sand. Bounded by latitudes 20.785191°S and 21.657125°S, and longitudes 147.214636°E and 148.20293°E.

concepts.label: Bulimba Plateau
concepts.definition: Dissected low sandstone plateau. Bounded by latitudes 16.095582°S and 17.875902°S, and longitudes 143.081442°E and 144.106039°E.

concepts.label: Bulloo Plain
concepts.definition: Floodplain and terminal floodout with pans and calcreted flats. Bounded by latitudes 26.604365°S and 29.816743°S, and longitudes 142.16261°E and 144.54148°E.

concepts.label: Bunda Plateau
concepts.definition: Covered karst plain of flat-lying limestone and calcrete with continuous cliff margin on south. Bounded by latitudes 29.607415°S and 33.614267°S, and longitudes 123.316086°E and 132.708298°E.

concepts.label: Bunya–Burnett Ranges
concepts.definition: Mountain ranges, rugged and dissected on granitic and metamorphic rocks in east, broader uplands and upland basins, partly on sedimentary rocks, in west. Bounded by latitudes 23.974239°S and 28.258758°S, and longitudes 150.000902°E and 153.390228°E.

concepts.label: Burdekin Hills and Lowlands
concepts.definition: In east, hills and footslopes on volcanic and mixed sedimentary rock with igneous intrusions; in west, dissected ferruginous-capped tablelands, mainly on sandstone. Bounded by latitudes 17.93373°S and 20.989406°S, and longitudes 144.983176°E and 147.300637°E.

concepts.label: Burdekin Plateaus
concepts.definition: Young basaltic plateaus with primary volcanic forms; north–south axial belt of rugged ranges, chiefly on granite and metamorphic rocks. Bounded by latitudes 17.931134°S and 20.683902°S, and longitudes 144.250643°E and 146.174385°E.

concepts.label: Burdekin Uplands Province
concepts.definition: Uplands and interior lowlands with a northwest–southeast trend parallel to and including coastal lowlands, dominated by the Burdekin River catchment. Bounded by latitudes 17.931134°S and 23.550995°S, and longitudes 142.789007°E and 148.424378°E.

concepts.label: Cape River Plains
concepts.definition: Plains with clay soils in the east, getting sandier to the west. Bounded by latitudes 20.256497°S and 21.629457°S, and longitudes 145.43318°E and 146.700712°E.

concepts.label: Gilberton Plateau
concepts.definition: Partly dissected sandstone plateau. Bounded by latitudes 18.673621°S and 20.810325°S, and longitudes 142.789007°E and 144.753677°E.

concepts.label: Hervey Tablelands
concepts.definition: Granitic uplands, rugged ranges on volcanic rocks and minor dissected ferruginous-capped plateaus forming steep eastern upland margin. Bounded by latitudes 18.006404°S and 21.038013°S, and longitudes 145.378047°E and 147.775731°E.

concepts.label: Townsville Lowlands
concepts.definition: Alluvial and deltaic plains with scattered high hills. Bounded by latitudes 18.419587°S and 21.082521°S, and longitudes 145.853738°E and 148.424378°E.

concepts.label: Cairns Ranges
concepts.definition: High ranges east of an interior lowland, consisting of coastal ranges, lowland corridors and bedrock islands. Bounded by latitudes 16.19637°S and 18.295249°S, and longitudes 145.194668°E and 146.15036°E.

concepts.label: Carborough Ranges
concepts.definition: Sandstone and basalt plateaus and lower rolling country on sedimentary and volcanic rocks. Bounded by latitudes 20.87373°S and 22.046464°S, and longitudes 148.654842°E and 147.957008°E.

concepts.label: Carlisle Plain
concepts.definition: Limestone plain with some salt lakes and sandplains. Bounded by latitudes 28.892723°S and 30.446088°S, and longitudes 124.581587°E and 130.545901°E.

concepts.label: Carnarvon Plain
concepts.definition: Alluvial plain and saline lake bed. Bounded by latitudes 23.307946°S and 25.857265°S, and longitudes 113.069389°E and 114.888397°E.

concepts.label: Carnegie Hills
concepts.definition: Sandstone tablelands, stony hardpan wash plains and salt lakes. Bounded by latitudes 25.068386°S and 27.020391°S, and longitudes 119.746412°E and 123.619433°E.

concepts.label: Carpentaria Fall Province
concepts.definition: Mainly dissected plateaus on subhorizontal resistant sandstones, mainly of the Sydney Basin. Bounded by latitudes 14.000811°S and 22.723370°S, and longitudes 133.138977°E and 140.930081°E.

concepts.label: Gulf Coastal Lowlands
concepts.definition: Ferruginous lowlands with alluvial plains; littoral plains with dunefields and sandplains in coastal areas; sandstone rises associated with islands. Bounded by latitudes 14.523394°S and 16.423096°S, and longitudes 135.042631°E and 137.743683°E.

concepts.label: Gulf Fall
concepts.definition: Dissected coastal fall, tabular ridges giving place to sloping plains and low hills seawards. Bounded by latitudes 14.000811°S and 19.840714°S, and longitudes 133.138977°E and 139.37918°E.

concepts.label: Isa Ridges
concepts.definition: Rugged parallel ranges and narrow lowlands on folded metamorphic rocks and granites. Bounded by latitudes 18.851091°S and 22.72337°S, and longitudes 138.904461°E and 140.930081°E.

concepts.label: Manangoora Plains
concepts.definition: Alluvial plains, minor ferruginized lowlands and islands, and littoral plains. Bounded by latitudes 14.6814°S and 17.876792°S, and longitudes 135.499634°E and 139.88736°E.

concepts.label: Carpentaria Lowlands Province
concepts.definition: Uplands and coastal areas of the western part of Cape York Peninsula, including the Great Escarpment. Bounded by latitudes 11.3029456°S and 20.864026°S, and longitudes 138.439832°E and 144.106039°E.

concepts.label: Clara–Mitchell Plains
concepts.definition: Sloping sandy alluvial plains with minor clay plains along distributary drainage. Bounded by latitudes 14.190464°S and 20.474045°S, and longitudes 141.018725°E and 143.786637°E.

concepts.label: Donors Tableland
concepts.definition: Stripped higher ferruginous surface on siltstone and sandstone. Bounded by latitudes 17.717099°S and 20.165739°S, and longitudes 139.765844°E and 140.965511°E.

concepts.label: Holroyd Plains
concepts.definition: Slightly dissected sandy plains, partly ferruginized. Bounded by latitudes 13.402537°S and 18.23227°S, and longitudes 141.542599°E and 143.844232°E.

concepts.label: Karumba Plain
concepts.definition: Littoral plain. Bounded by latitudes 13.3698°S and 17.962122°S, and longitudes 139.23281°E and 141.810222°E.

concepts.label: Merluna Plain
concepts.definition: Undulating clay plains with ferruginous rises. Bounded by latitudes 12.206185°S and 14.900153°S, and longitudes 141.904938°E and 142.966639°E.

concepts.label: Normanton Tableland
concepts.definition: Stripped higher ferruginous surface on siltstone and sandstone. Bounded by latitudes 17.587587°S and 17.97482°S, and longitudes 140.796183°E and 141.127611°E.

concepts.label: Weipa Plateau
concepts.definition: Bauxite-capped plateau on clayey sand and sandstone. Bounded by latitudes 11.302946°S and 15.2219°S, and longitudes 141.55867°E and 142.862072°E.

concepts.label: Wondoola Plain
concepts.definition: Clay floodplain. Bounded by latitudes 17.647243°S and 20.864026°S, and longitudes 140.296911°E and 142.749084°E.

concepts.label: Ceduna Dunefield
concepts.definition: Low limestone dune ridges; small granitic islands with dunes. Bounded by latitudes 31.266549°S and 34.815689°S, and longitudes 131.151728°E and 136.416593°E.

concepts.label: Central Australian Ranges Province
concepts.definition: Sandstone and limestone plains, coastal plains, and dunes. Bounded by latitudes 21.056309°S and 27.184211°S, and longitudes 126.478709°E and 137.029688°E.

concepts.label: Central Ranges
concepts.definition: Fold complex of prominent east–west ranges, mainly of quartzite; lowlands on limestone and shale with gravel terraces. Bounded by latitudes 22.96049°S and 25.498264°S, and longitudes 130.39181°E and 135.752895°E.

concepts.label: Kulgera Hills
concepts.definition: Sandy granitic plains with prominent hills. Bounded by latitudes 25.639996°S and 27.184211°S, and longitudes 132.134532°E and 134.390766°E.

concepts.label: Northern Alice Plains
concepts.definition: Granitic plains with ferruginous cappings; wash plains with sandplain, minor longitudinal dunes, and calcrete-rimmed salt lakes in lowest parts. Bounded by latitudes 21.969075°S and 23.84755°S, and longitudes 130.291359°E and 137.029688°E.

concepts.label: Northern Alice Ranges
concepts.definition: Ranges and rounded summits, partly granitic and partly quartzite and sandstone. Bounded by latitudes 21.056309°S and 22.824971°S, and longitudes 130.346608°E and 136.455643°E.

concepts.label: Todd Plains
concepts.definition: Stony lowland of calcareous conglomerate and other weak rocks, with extensive low dunes; anticlinal sandstone ridges. Bounded by latitudes 23.684565°S and 24.363842°S, and longitudes 131.733121°E and 134.240118°E.

concepts.label: Warburton Ranges
concepts.definition: Ranges and hills of basic volcanic rocks and granite surrounded by hardpan wash plains and some sandplains. Bounded by latitudes 25.73046°S and 26.370232°S, and longitudes 126.478709°E and 127.596266°E.

concepts.label: Western Desert Ranges
concepts.definition: Dissected sandstone, granitic and volcanic ranges with prominent escarpments; separated by sandplains with dunes of hardpan wash plains. Bounded by latitudes 24.475585°S and 26.511586°S, and longitudes 126.724991°E and 132.489328°E.

concepts.label: Central Lowlands Province
concepts.definition: Hills and plateaus on resistant rocks, some alluvial plains. Bounded by latitudes 20.026174°S and 32.980276°S, and longitudes 133.128183°E and 152.319707°E.

concepts.label: Charleville Tableland
concepts.definition: Low sandy tableland of weathered sandstone and shale. Bounded by latitudes 24.692152°S and 29.663575°S, and longitudes 145.063991°E and 150.59594°E.

concepts.label: Condamine Lowlands
concepts.definition: Undulating clay lowlands on siltstone and low sandstone hills; floodplains. Bounded by latitudes 26.454383°S and 28.718057°S, and longitudes 150.121911°E and 152.319707°E.

concepts.label: Cooper Plain
concepts.definition: Floodplain. Bounded by latitudes 24.668078°S and 28.053456°S, and longitudes 141.195363°E and 143.352939°E.

concepts.label: Denison Ranges
concepts.definition: Bevelled low ridges of folded metamorphic rocks. Bounded by latitudes 27.968561°S and 28.823432°S, and longitudes 135.805714°1E and 36.211969°E.

concepts.label: Diamantina Plain
concepts.definition: Floodplain. Bounded by latitudes 23.14687°S and 27.665199°S, and longitudes 138.318838°E and 141.696441°E.

concepts.label: Eromanga Lowlands
concepts.definition: Stony plains with silcrete-capped mesas, minor alluvial and sandy tracts. Bounded by latitudes 21.552601°S and 28.977524°S, and longitudes 138.754777°E and 146.15178°E.

concepts.label: Eyre Creek Plain
concepts.definition: Floodplain. Bounded by latitudes 21.61642°S and 25.11425°S, and longitudes 138.617785°E and 140.713522°E.

concepts.label: Eyre–Frome Plains
concepts.definition: Major salt lakes and adjacent alluvial plains; minor stony plains and longitudinal dunes. Bounded by latitudes 27.842049°S and 32.155274°S, and longitudes 136.269228°E and 141.349675°E.

concepts.label: Grey Range
concepts.definition: Silcrete-capped tablelands. Bounded by latitudes 27.649476°S and 30.262826°S, and longitudes 141.274586°E and 143.413904°E.

concepts.label: Innamincka Plains
concepts.definition: Eolian sandplain with west- to north-northwest-trending seif dunes, and numerous claypans and alluvial areas (floodout of Cooper Creek). Bounded by latitudes 26.326344°S and 28.826029°S, and longitudes 139.207682°E and 140.814965°E.

concepts.label: Jericho Plain
concepts.definition: Sandplain. Bounded by latitudes 22.028735°S and 24.587845°S, and longitudes 145.097648°E and 146.30823°E.

concepts.label: Lightning Ridge Lowland
concepts.definition: Stony plains with minor silcrete-capped mesas. Bounded by latitudes 28.483544°S and 30.072168°S, and longitudes 147.350717°E and 148.565744°E.

concepts.label: Maranoa Lowland
concepts.definition: Sandplain with low sandstone hills. Bounded by latitudes 23.586687°S and 26.359875°S, and longitudes 145.814341°E and 148.427454°E.

concepts.label: Nulty Springs Lowlands
concepts.definition: Rolling downs and lowlands with hard red ridges and flats. Ferruginized regolith quite different from surrounding alluvial and sand plains. Bounded by latitudes 28.601625°S and 29.990434°S, and longitudes 145.582829°E and 147.063709°E.

concepts.label: Oodnadatta Tablelands
concepts.definition: Silcrete-capped low tablelands. Bounded by latitudes 25.658357°S and 30.379555°S, and longitudes 133.128183°E and 137.362127°E.

concepts.label: Paroo Plain
concepts.definition: Sandplain with alluvial flats and claypans. Bounded by latitudes 27.294256°S and 30.373204°S, and longitudes 142.824185°E and 145.410658°E.

concepts.label: Simpson Desert Dunefield
concepts.definition: South–north longitudinal dunes with sandstone ridges in the west and playas in the south. Bounded by latitudes 23.06095°S and 27.714416°S, and longitudes 134.394858°E and 139.367053°E.

concepts.label: Simpson Desert Plains
concepts.definition: Eolian dunefield (north-northwest trending seif dunes), with numerous claypans, Eolian sand, fine lacustrine and alluvial deposits. Bounded by latitudes 25.595982°S and 29.261594°S, and longitudes 136.70049°E and 138.799131°E.

concepts.label: St George Plain
concepts.definition: Sandplain, residual sand on old alluvium. Bounded by latitudes 26.233764°S and 28.997905°S, and longitudes 145.965588°E and 148.903252°E.

concepts.label: Strzelecki Desert Plains
concepts.definition: Longitudinal dunes and stony plains, minor claypans and floodplains. Bounded by latitudes 26.98873°S and 31.370752°S, and longitudes 138.673846°E and 142.857612°E.

concepts.label: Sturt Desert Plains
concepts.definition: Stony plains with minor sand ridges. Bounded by latitudes 25.464829°S and 28.340281°S, and longitudes 138.396075°E and 141.955651°E.

concepts.label: Upper Darling Plains
concepts.definition: Floodplains of centripetal anastomosing rivers. Bounded by latitudes 27.928535°S and 32.980276°S, and longitudes 145.891529°E and 150.867872°E.

concepts.label: Warrego Plains
concepts.definition: Main and distributary floodplains, sandplains with claypans. Bounded by latitudes 26.702518°S and 30.216786°S, and longitudes 144.786896°E and 146.924643°E.

concepts.label: Warwick Lowland
concepts.definition: Stony plains with silcrete-capped mesas. Bounded by latitudes 28.23727°S and 32.095795°S, and longitudes 141.735532°E and 145.594392°E.

concepts.label: Whelen Lowlands
concepts.definition: Undulating clay plains with silcrete-capped mesas in east. Bounded by latitudes 23.061938°S and 24.495791°S, and longitudes 138.73827°E and 139.678729°E.

concepts.label: Winton–Blackall Downs
concepts.definition: Undulating clay plains. Bounded by latitudes 20.026174°S and 26.040646°S, and longitudes 140.601093°E and 140.601093°146.996283°E.

concepts.label: Chichester Range
concepts.definition: Narrow range of hills and dissected plateaus on basalt and sedimentary rocks. Bounded by latitudes 20.809919°S and 22.584392°S, and longitudes 116.050834°E and 120.103237°E.

concepts.label: Clarence Fall
concepts.definition: Dissected plateau margin on granite and metamorphic rocks. Bounded by latitudes 28.328417°S and 30.346845°S, and longitudes 152.104399°E and 153.269257°E.

concepts.label: Clarence Lowlands
concepts.definition: Coastal lowlands on weak sedimentary rocks, with littoral and alluvial plains. Bounded by latitudes 28.807524°S and 29.989761°S, and longitudes 152.819404°1E and 53.607544°E.

concepts.label: Cobar Plains
concepts.definition: Plains with remnants of silcrete and low sandstone ridges, sand cover in west, with west–east longitudinal dunes. Bounded by latitudes 30.118828°S and 34.282174°S, and longitudes 144.233465°E and 148.388534°E.

concepts.label: Coleman Plateau
concepts.definition: Rolling sandy granitic plateau with low ridges of metamorphic rocks, includes Great Escarpment in the east. Bounded by latitudes 13.835726°S and 15.597455°S, and longitudes 142.863628°E and 143.636095°E.

concepts.label: Condobolin Plains
concepts.definition: Plains of gravel and sandy alluvium. Bounded by latitudes 32.918201°S and 34.456489°S, and longitudes 146.850571°E and 148.371177°E.

concepts.label: Connors Ranges
concepts.definition: Rounded mountain ranges on the dissected eastern margin of the uplands. Bounded by latitudes 20.200058°S and 24.52482°S, and longitudes 151.051282°E and 147.478079°E.

concepts.label: Cooktown Ranges
concepts.definition: Deeply dissected sandstone plateaus with mountain ranges of granite and metamorphic rocks to east, small bedrock islands. Bounded by latitudes 14.16453°S and 16.665559°S, and longitudes 144.020835°E and 145.476486°E.

concepts.label: Coonana–Ragged Plateau
concepts.definition: Undulating plains with low hills of granite and metamorphic rocks; calcretes and scattered small salt lakes along shallow valleys. Bounded by latitudes 31.464241°S and 32.769595°S, and longitudes 122.738547°E and 123.854534°E.

concepts.label: Coorong Plain
concepts.definition: Coastal barrier, lagoons, and limestone dunes. Bounded by latitudes 35.117234°S and 36.472662°S, and longitudes 138.723209°E and 140.464118°E.

concepts.label: Cotherstone Plateau
concepts.definition: Dissected sandstone plateau. Bounded by latitudes 21.939506°S and 23.069832°S, and longitudes 147.812939°E and 147.812939°148.508975°E.

concepts.label: Couchman Uplands
concepts.definition: Undulating to hilly lower plateaus, on basalt, shale and sandstone. Bounded by latitudes 13.68923°S and 17.024323°S, and longitudes 125.481484°E and 127.538008°E.

concepts.label: Cumberland Lowland
concepts.definition: Undulating to low hilly country, mainly on shale. Bounded by latitudes 33.557374°S and 34.198768°S, and longitudes 150.576734°E and 151.287033°E.

concepts.label: Cunningham Slopes
concepts.definition: Ridges and valleys in metamorphic rocks. Bounded by latitudes 27.964578°S and 31.723076°S, and longitudes 150.189184°E and 151.877246°E.

concepts.label: Daly Basin
concepts.definition: Lowlands of limestone and weak sedimentary rocks, including alluvial plains; minor laterite-capped plateaus. Bounded by latitudes 13.07496°S and 15.095786°S, and longitudes 130.666251°E and 132.613331°E.

concepts.label: Dampier Tablelands
concepts.definition: Low sandstone tableland, partially laterized and with extensive sandplain cover. Bounded by latitudes 16.27652°S and 18.132163°S, and longitudes 122.09185°E and 123.645747°E.

concepts.label: Dandaragan Tablelands
concepts.definition: Dissected ferruginous plateaus and hills on sedimentary rocks with areas of sandplain; extensive coastal dune system in west. Bounded by latitudes 27.577965°S and 31.661904°S, and longitudes 114.575798°E and 116.093696°E.

concepts.label: Darling Range
concepts.definition: High ferruginous plateau; steep western fall and deeply incised valleys of oceanward drainage exposing granitic basement. Bounded by latitudes 30.832177°S and 34.111033°S, and longitudes 115.764879°E and 117.198305°E.

concepts.label: De Grey Lowlands
concepts.definition: Floodplains and deltaic plains with stony plains and sandplains; tidal flats and some metamorphic, volcanic and granitic hills and islands. Bounded by latitudes 20.014311°S and 21.288328°S, and longitudes 116.191078°E and 120.882896°E.

concepts.label: Donnybrook Lowland
concepts.definition: Low, moderately dissected ferruginous plateau on down-faulted sedimentary rocks; swampy coastal plain in the south. Bounded by latitudes 33.344415°S and 34.542133°S, and longitudes 115.096757°E and 115.843828°E.

concepts.label: Drummond Uplands
concepts.definition: Ridges and valleys on sandstone and minor metamorphic rocks; rolling country on granite. Bounded by latitudes 22.386559°S and 24.203562°S, and longitudes 146.602107°E and 147.737691°E.

concepts.label: East Tasmanian Hills
concepts.definition: Fault block hills and mountains on dolerite, sandstone, and mudstone, with granite residuals, ria coast. Bounded by latitudes 40.901944°S and 43.860401°S, and longitudes 146.354357°E and 148.359406°E.

concepts.label: East Victorian Uplands
concepts.definition: Dissected high plateaus on various resistant rocks, with isolated high plains. Bounded by latitudes 35.300222°S and 38.148959°S, and longitudes 144.986927°E and 149.765915°E.

concepts.label: Eastern Upland Division
concepts.definition: The eastern uplands of Australia. Landform patterns reflect structural contrasts. Meridional folding and faulting are reflected in a general north–south grain of relief. It includes both the Great Divide and the Great Escarpment. Bounded by latitudes 9.141290°S and 43.860401°S, and longitudes 141.020610°E and 153.638336°E.

concepts.label: Fitzroy Uplands Province
concepts.definition: Low ranges and tablelands with lowlands and some plateaus. Bounded by latitudes 20.060381°S and 25.991111°S, and longitudes 146.069187°E and 151.600625°E.

concepts.label: Great Barrier Reef Province
concepts.definition: Erosional plains with sand plains, lakes and alluvial valley floors; breakaways. Bounded by latitudes 9.141290°S and 24.096460°S, and longitudes 141.419143°E and 152.394791°E.

concepts.label: Kosciuszkan Uplands Province
concepts.definition: Mainly depositional plains around the southeast of the Gulf of Carpentaria. Bounded by latitudes 33.2043171°S and 39.522332°S, and longitudes 141.020610°E and 150.849319°E.

concepts.label: Macquarie Uplands Province
concepts.definition: Low plateaus, sand plains and dune fields. Bounded by latitudes 30.370879°S and 35.303008°S, and longitudes 147.660206°E and 152.205841°E.

concepts.label: New England–Moreton Uplands Province
concepts.definition: Adelaide Hills and lowland areas to Broken Hill. Bounded by latitudes 23.974239°S and 32.756200°S, and longitudes 148.175259°E and 153.638336°E.

concepts.label: Peninsular Uplands Province
concepts.definition: Interior lowlands, mainly internally draining. Bounded by latitudes 9.354060°S and 19.560565°S, and longitudes 141.718155°E and 146.150360°E.

concepts.label: Tasmanian Uplands Province
concepts.definition: Dissected plateaus and tablelands, some alluvial plains. Bounded by latitudes 39.435318°S and 43.860401°S, and longitudes 143.819443°E and 148.498795°E.

concepts.label: Eighty Mile Plain
concepts.definition: Coastal plains and dunes with some estuarine plains. Bounded by latitudes 17.842708°S and 20.187084°S, and longitudes 118.807411°E and 122.745733°E.

concepts.label: Einasleigh Plains
concepts.definition: Undulating to irregular plains on granite and metamorphic rocks. Bounded by latitudes 18.002822°S and 19.422524°S, and longitudes 143.803457°E and 144.677042°E.

concepts.label: Expedition Scarplands
concepts.definition: Rugged plateaus and ridges on sandstone. Bounded by latitudes 23.599106°S and 25.991111°S, and longitudes 148.688263°E and 150.403674°E.

concepts.label: Eyre Dunefield
concepts.definition: Stable northwest–southeast longitudinal dunes, locally broken by granite hills and ridges of metamorphic rocks. Bounded by latitudes 32.373119°S and 33.74147°S, and longitudes 135.14687°E and 137.58727°E.

concepts.label: Eyre Peninsula Province
concepts.definition: Lowlands and plains sloping to the Gulf of Carpentaria. Bounded by latitudes 29.346210°S and 29.346210°S, and longitudes 131.151728°E and 137.630649°E.

concepts.label: Gairdner Plain
concepts.definition: Alluvial plains and salt lakes with some dunes. Bounded by latitudes 29.34621°S and 32.333142°S, and longitudes 132.491585°E and 137.630649°E.

concepts.label: Gawler–Cleve Ranges
concepts.definition: Rounded ranges of acid volcanic rocks and hills of metamorphic rocks. Bounded by latitudes 31.457066°S and 32.789524°S, and longitudes 134.814071°E and 137.502419°E.

concepts.label: Lincoln Hills
concepts.definition: Low granite hills and plains extending as headlands and inlets. Bounded by latitudes 33.599126°S and 35.340549°S, and longitudes 135.027893°E and 136.969757°E.

concepts.label: Fitzroy Plains
concepts.definition: Floodplains, sandplains, and broad estuarine plains. Bounded by latitudes 16.577756°S and 18.815086°S, and longitudes 123.515999°E and 126.029559°E.

concepts.label: Fitzroy Ranges
concepts.definition: Scattered tablelands and ranges of sedimentary rocks and extensive outcrop plains and sandplain and east–west longitudinal dunes. Bounded by latitudes 18.101217°S and 19.371511°S, and longitudes 123.760104°E and 127.802019°E.

concepts.label: Mackenzie–Dawson Lowlands
concepts.definition: Floodplains, clay plains and sandy bedrock lowlands. Bounded by latitudes 21.604907°S and 25.447947°S, and longitudes 147.931586°E and 150.648043°E.

concepts.label: Nagoa Scarplands
concepts.definition: Sandstone strike ridges and clay valleys. Bounded by latitudes 22.7778°S and 25.515761°S, and 146.069187°longitudes E and 148.035313°E.

concepts.label: Scartwater Hills
concepts.definition: Hills, ridges and valleys on sandstone and minor metamorphic rocks. Bounded by latitudes 20.765358°S and 22.208163°S, and longitudes 147.394594°E and 146.158662°E.

concepts.label: Springsure–Clermont Plateaus
concepts.definition: Moderately dissected low plateaus, mainly basalt with minor sandstone. Bounded by latitudes 22.215523°S and 24.600405°S, and longitudes 147.266649°E and 149.020632°E.

concepts.label: Townshend Ranges and Lowlands
concepts.definition: Mosaic of mountains, hills, lowlands and peninsulas. Lowlands include alluvial plains, tidal flats and coastal dunes. Bounded by latitudes 20.060381°S and 22.064371°S, and longitudes 149.523331°E and 148.368599°E.

concepts.label: Flinders–Lofty Ranges
concepts.definition: Complex fold belt of prominent ranges in north, chiefly quartzite with vales on weaker rocks; stepped fault blocks and islands in south, mainly of weathered metamorphic rocks with ferruginous cappings. Bounded by latitudes 29.36382°S and 36.396648°S, and longitudes 136.532745°E and 139.788214°E.

concepts.label: Fortescue Valley
concepts.definition: Mainly alluvial lowland with hardpan wash plains and sandplain, possibly a graben. Bounded by latitudes 21.574089°S and 23.432007°S, and longitudes 116.768643°E and 120.576764°E.

concepts.label: Garnet Uplands
concepts.definition: Hilly uplands with dissected greywacke and volcanics in north and undulating country on granite and metamorphic rocks in the south. Bounded by latitudes 15.929353°S and 18.150512°S, and longitudes 143.981117°E and 145.708606°E.

concepts.label: Gibson Desert Plains
concepts.definition: Sandy or stony ferruginous plains. Bounded by latitudes 22.164247°S and 27.280427°S, and longitudes 123.848425°E and 127.018453°E.

concepts.label: Gilbert Hills
concepts.definition: Rolling country on granite, and ridges and valleys on metamorphic rocks. Bounded by latitudes 17.768153°S and 18.883566°S, and longitudes 142.838231°E and 143.833715°E.

concepts.label: Gippsland Plain
concepts.definition: Terraced plains with sand and gravels. Bounded by latitudes 37.66496°S and 38.762749°S, and longitudes 146.356378°E and 149.501251°E.

concepts.label: Glengarry Hills
concepts.definition: Hills, hardpan wash plains and stony plains on sedimentary, granitic, and volcanic rocks. Bounded by latitudes 24.917901°S and 26.802447°S, and longitudes 118.157898°E and 120.763266°E.

concepts.label: Goulburn Corridor
concepts.definition: Broad valley floors on weaker rocks, overlooked by irregular dissected plateaus. Bounded by latitudes 32.171759°S and 32.771659°S, and longitudes 149.634664°E and 150.629272°E.

concepts.label: North Reefs
concepts.definition: Patch reefs with semicontinuous outer barrier. Bounded by latitudes 9.14129°S and 14.22723°S, and longitudes 141.419144°E and 144.063858°E.

concepts.label: South Reefs
concepts.definition: Patch reefs with bedrock islands and discontinuous outer barrier. Bounded by latitudes 14.05041°S and 24.09646°S, and longitudes 144.202148°E and 152.394791°E.

concepts.label: Great Sandy Desert Dunefield
concepts.definition: East–west longitudinal dunes and minor salt lakes. Bounded by latitudes 17.863681°S and 25.983593°S, and longitudes 119.380411°E and 130.572816°E.

concepts.label: Great Victoria Desert Dunes
concepts.definition: West–east longitudinal dunes, broken by low tablelands and ridges in the northwest. Bounded by latitudes 25.158119°S and 32.196006°S, and longitudes 122.540793°E and 135.621357°E.

concepts.label: Greenough Hills
concepts.definition: Dissected ferruginous plateaus and hills of sandstone and shale over granite, extensive sandplain on dissected plateau. Bounded by latitudes 27.376333°S and 28.987°S, and longitudes 113.588676°E and 115.131853°E.

concepts.label: Gregory Range
concepts.definition: Dissected sandstone plateau and hilly country on acid volcanic rocks. Bounded by latitudes 17.929322°S and 19.027512°S, and longitudes 142.174496°E and 142.174496°142.978174°E.

concepts.label: Gulfs Ranges Province
concepts.definition: Outer barrier reef, patch reefs and some high islands. Bounded by latitudes 29.363820°S and 36.396648°S, and longitudes 136.421646°E and 142.138110°E.

concepts.label: Olary Spur
concepts.definition: Low hill belt of folded crystalline and sedimentary rocks. Bounded by latitudes 31.674194°S and 33.41426°S, and longitudes 139.010067°E and 140.74781°E.

concepts.label: Torrens–Gulf Plains
concepts.definition: Salt lake and bahadas in north; alluvial and littoral plains in south; northwest–southeast longitudinal dunes, mainly stabilized. Bounded by latitudes 30.025979°S and 35.030416°S, and longitudes 137.205397°E and 138.743677°E.

concepts.label: Yorke Peninsula
concepts.definition: Undulating lowland of folded crystalline and metamorphic rocks; cover of calcrete and stabilized northwest–southeast longitudinal dunes. Bounded by latitudes 33.3832°S and 35.907952°S, and longitudes 136.421646°E and 138.332656°E.

concepts.label: Gunnedah Lowland
concepts.definition: Alluvial plains, sandstone ridges and hills of basic intrusive rocks. Bounded by latitudes 30.619349°S and 31.74602°S, and longitudes 149.748673°E and 150.600731°E.

concepts.label: Halls Creek Ridges
concepts.definition: Ranges and rounded hills on sedimentary (and some volcanic) rocks. Bounded by latitudes 17.004139°S and 19.099638°S, and longitudes 126.760108°E and 128.833139°E.

concepts.label: Hamersley Plateaus
concepts.definition: Dissected bold plateaus and ranges of flat lying or moderately folded sandstone, quartzite, and volcanic rocks. Bounded by latitudes 21.576916°S and 23.515019°S, and longitudes 116.080361°E and 120.263465°E.

concepts.label: Hawkesbury–Shoalhaven Plateaus
concepts.definition: Deeply dissected sandstone plateaus. Bounded by latitudes 32.414976°S and 35.303008°S, and longitudes 149.85788°E and 151.706956°E.

concepts.label: Hume Slopes
concepts.definition: Ridges and minor tablelands stepping down westwards and breaking into detached hills with intervening alluvial valley floors. Some strong structural control on landforms. Bounded by latitudes 33.204317°S and 36.238821°S, and longitudes 146.159809°E and 148.600195°E.

concepts.label: Hunter Valley
concepts.definition: Undulating to low hilly country on weak rocks, with alluvial and sandy littoral plains. Bounded by latitudes 31.942578°S and 33.079382°S, and longitudes 150.452434°E and 152.205841°E.

concepts.label: Interior Lowland Division
concepts.definition: Younger intracratonic basins with relatively flat sedimentary strata. Bounded by latitudes 11.302946°S and 38.411320°S, and longitudes 133.128183°E and 152.319707°E.

concepts.label: Murray Lowlands Province
concepts.definition: Mountains and plateaus ranging from the highest point in Australia to the coast. Bounded by latitudes 29.957591°S and 38.411320°S, and longitudes 138.723209°E and 148.3885345°E.

concepts.label: Israelite Plain
concepts.definition: Narrow coastal plain with extensive dunes. Bounded by latitudes 32.926917°S and 34.108841°S, and longitudes 123.498621°E and 124.49038°E.

concepts.label: Ivanhoe Plains
concepts.definition: Plains with low west–east stabilized longitudinal dunes and sandplain, small pans with lunettes, minor sandstone ridges, floodplains. Bounded by latitudes 31.291259°S and 34.470967°S, and longitudes 139.760816°E and 145.562091°E.

concepts.label: Jardine Uplands
concepts.definition: Locally dissected rolling sandstone upland with transgressive coastal dunes along eastern margin. Bounded by latitudes 10.86809°S and 12.808629°S, and longitudes 141.718155°E and 143.244873°E.

concepts.label: Kennedy Range
concepts.definition: Dissected sandstone plateau with partial ferruginous cappings, covered by longitudinal dunes. Bounded by latitudes 24.082236°S and 24.974937°S, and longitudes 114.76144°E and 115.231334°E.

concepts.label: Kimberley Plateau
concepts.definition: Sandstone plateaus (deeply dissected in places) with tabular high summits; some basaltic plateau; ria coast and islands to the northwest. Bounded by latitudes 13.93137°S and 17.828259°S, and longitudes 123.547882°E and 128.233673°E.

concepts.label: Kimberley Province
concepts.definition: Hilly and mountainous, high relief. Bounded by latitudes 13.689230°S and 19.371511°S, and longitudes 122.091850°E and 128.948688°E.

concepts.label: Napier Limestone Ranges
concepts.definition: Limestone tableland and intricately dissected bevelled ridges; separated by plains and rocky karst surfaces with box valleys. Bounded by latitudes 16.85309°S and 18.776871°S, and longitudes 123.802612°E and 126.379111°E.

concepts.label: Richenda Foothills
concepts.definition: Rounded hills and ridges and lowlands on a belt of granite and folded metamorphic and sedimentary rocks with minor basalt. Bounded by latitudes 15.5098°S and 18.099116°S, and longitudes 123.151871°E and 126.579422°E.

concepts.label: Springvale Foothills
concepts.definition: Granitic, volcanic, and sedimentary hills with minor undulating plains. Bounded by latitudes 16.676474°S and 18.984041°S, and longitudes 126.225017°E and 128.479206°E.

concepts.label: Wunaamin Miliwundi and Durack Ranges
concepts.definition: Prominent ranges of dipping volcanic and granitic rocks and sandstones rimming the main Kimberley Plateau. The name of this physiographic region was changed from Leopold–Durack Ranges following the renaming of the King Leopold Ranges to Wunaamin Miliwundi Ranges in 2020. Bounded by latitudes 15.528314°S and 18.727432°S, and longitudes 124.447889°E and 128.948688°E.

concepts.label: Monaro Fall
concepts.definition: Deeply dissected steeply sloping plateau margin in metamorphics and granite. Bounded in the west by the Great Escarpment. Bounded by latitudes 34.924032°S and 37.756359°S, and longitudes 149.336751°E and 150.849319°E.

concepts.label: Monaro Tableland
concepts.definition: Undulating upland plains with some tabular basalt relief and granite tors. Bounded by latitudes 35.97531°S and 37.778511°S, and longitudes 148.442004°E and 149.431793°E.

concepts.label: South Victorian Uplands
concepts.definition: Low fault blocks, mainly of tilted and dissected sandstone; granite hills and islands, in two parts either side of Port Phillip Bay. Bounded by latitudes 37.991314°S and 39.522331°S, and longitudes 143.134495°E and 147.030334°E.

concepts.label: Tinderry–Gourock Ranges
concepts.definition: High hill chains of granite, sandstone and greywacke, moderately dissected, some fault lines. Bounded by latitudes 35.256032°S and 36.690353°S, and longitudes 149.140357°E and 149.709269°E.

concepts.label: Werriwa Tablelands
concepts.definition: Upland plains with separating strike-aligned hills, closed lake basins. Bounded by latitudes 34.465318°S and 35.654329°S, and longitudes 148.750323°E and 150.152407°E.

concepts.label: West Victorian Plains
concepts.definition: Plains mainly on basalt lavas with many volcanic forms and lakes, partly on weak sedimentary rocks. Bounded by latitudes 37.412111°S and 38.688694°S, and longitudes 141.282568°E and 145.248168°E.

concepts.label: West Victorian Uplands
concepts.definition: Moderately high plateaus and strike ridges. Bounded by latitudes 36.207532°S and 38.426071°S, and longitudes 141.02061°E and 145.220636°E.

concepts.label: Lakes Plateau
concepts.definition: High dolerite plateau with many lakes, glaciated in west. Bounded by latitudes 41.539578°S and 42.440651°S, and longitudes 146.10101°E and 147.345993°E.

concepts.label: Laura Plain
concepts.definition: Soft sedimentary rock lowlands, alluvial plains and coastal plain. Bounded by latitudes 13.767155°S and 15.767124°S, and longitudes 143.425719°E and 144.74613°E.

concepts.label: Leemans Sandplain
concepts.definition: Sandplain with some gravel plains, mesas, and small salt lakes. Bounded by latitudes 26.492127°S and 30.662666°S, and longitudes 121.492232°E and 123.932368°E.

concepts.label: Leeuwin Peninsula
concepts.definition: Narrow granitic horst ridge with calcareous dune system on western margin and dissected ferruginous plateau in the east. Bounded by latitudes 33.530159°S and 34.38374°S, and longitudes 114.975029°E and 115.193681°E.

concepts.label: Little Sandy Desert
concepts.definition: East–west longitudinal dunes and minor salt lakes. Bounded by latitudes 22.197759°S and 25.806083°S, and longitudes 119.890907°E and 123.269001°E.

concepts.label: Liverpool–Barrington Plateaus
concepts.definition: Dissected basaltic plateaus. Bounded by latitudes 31.348304°S and 32.323859°S, and longitudes 151.122234°E and 152.52866°E.

concepts.label: Lower Darling Plain
concepts.definition: Floodplain and lunette lakes. Bounded by latitudes 29.957591°S and 34.276252°S, and longitudes 140.654329°E and 146.268179°E.

concepts.label: Macdonald Sandplain
concepts.definition: Mainly sandplain with dune-fringed salt lakes. Bounded by latitudes 23.080796°S and 23.766894°S, and longitudes 128.483625°E and 131.01078°E.

concepts.label: Macleay–Barrington Fall
concepts.definition: Plateau flank dissected into narrow strike ridges and valleys. Bounded by latitudes 30.320413°S and 32.7562°S, and longitudes 150.880601°E and 153.130187°E.

concepts.label: Merriwa Plateau
concepts.definition: Rolling basalt upland with sandstone cliffs. Bounded by latitudes 31.530666°S and 32.28168°S, and longitudes 149.541224°E and 151.203041°E.

concepts.label: Mitchell Slopes
concepts.definition: Tablelands stepping down to west and breaking into detached hills. Bounded by latitudes 30.370879°S and 34.812456°S, and longitudes 147.660206°E and 150.043234°E.

concepts.label: Warrumbungle Peaks
concepts.definition: Dissected volcanic pile with plugs. Bounded by latitudes 30.941727°S and 31.553229°S, and longitudes 148.737898°E and 149.26379°E.

concepts.label: Mallee Dunefield
concepts.definition: Fixed west–east calcareous longitudinal dunes. Bounded by latitudes 33.819057°S and 36.306182°S, and longitudes 139.157554°E and 143.832952°E.

concepts.label: Maryborough Lowland
concepts.definition: Lowland on weak sedimentary rocks, partly dune covered including K'gari (formerly Fraser Island). Bounded by latitudes 24.144118°S and 26.481847°S, and longitudes 151.764481°E and 153.358566°E.

concepts.label: Midlands Plain
concepts.definition: Fault-bounded lowland (graben) on weathered sediments, with some dolerite, sedimentary and metamorphic hills. Bounded by latitudes 41.063358°S and 42.191972°S, and longitudes 146.48604°E and 147.55712°E.

concepts.label: Millicent Plain
concepts.definition: Parallel dune limestone ridges with intervening swamps; closed karst depressions and young volcanoes in southeast. Bounded by latitudes 36.374543°S and 38.41132°S, and longitudes 139.670547°E and 141.670883°E.

concepts.label: Moreton Lowland
concepts.definition: Lowland on weak sedimentary rocks, with prominent volcanic plugs, includes dune islands. Bounded by latitudes 26.613991°S and 28.19735°S, and longitudes 152.838542°E and 153.579895°E.

concepts.label: Murchison Plateau
concepts.definition: Sandplains and hardpan wash plains with outgoing drainage and salt lakes, broken by ridges of metamorphic rocks and granite. Bounded by latitudes 25.167211°S and 29.930099°S, and longitudes 115.212771°E and 122.928611°E.

concepts.label: Riverine Plain
concepts.definition: Alluvial plain. Bounded by latitudes 32.532551°S and 36.949484°S, and longitudes 142.826891°E and 146.761128°E.

concepts.label: West–Turkey Plains
concepts.definition: Plains with variable dune cover, claypans, saline swamps, and intermittent lakes in low-lying areas. Bounded by latitudes 31.813614°S and 34.798565°S, and longitudes 139.082269°E and 142.942363°E.

concepts.label: Wimmera Plain
concepts.definition: Eolian and alluvial sandplain, minor low sandstone ridges. Bounded by latitudes 35.255883°S and 37.299233°S, and longitudes E and 140.352986°143.308516°E.

concepts.label: Nandewar Peaks
concepts.definition: Dissected volcanic pile. Bounded by latitudes 29.543995°S and 30.836196°S, and longitudes 149.760031°E and150.381189°E.

concepts.label: Taroom Hills
concepts.definition: Sandstone ridges and shale lowlands. Bounded by latitudes 24.56042°S and 26.835811°S, and longitudes 148.175259°E and 151.344084°E.

concepts.label: Tenterfield Plateau
concepts.definition: Undulating granitic plateau with higher residuals including basalt cappings. Bounded by latitudes 28.190536°S and 31.613426°S, and longitudes 150.916329°E and 152.900874°E.

concepts.label: Toowoomba Plateau
concepts.definition: Basaltic plateau terminating southeast in dissected volcanic pile (Mount Warning). Bounded by latitudes 25.993017°S and 28.967651°S, and longitudes 151.19928°E and 153.638336°E.

concepts.label: Newcastle Ranges
concepts.definition: Rugged hills on acid volcanic, granite and metamorphic rocks. Bounded by latitudes 17.141193°S and 19.560565°S, and longitudes 143.368822°E and 144.468041°E.

concepts.label: North Australian Plateaus Province
concepts.definition: Low ranges, plateaus, tablelands and plains. Bounded by latitudes 10.903421°S and 18.623043°S, and longitudes 127.709584°E and 136.984985°E.

concepts.label: Ord–Victoria Plateaus
concepts.definition: Dissected plateaus, mainly basaltic but partly of sandstone with local ferruginous cappings. Bounded by latitudes 13.216329°S and 18.623043°S, and longitudes 127.709584°E and 132.195317°E.

concepts.label: Pine Creek Ridges
concepts.definition: Rounded ridges of folded metamorphic rocks with granitic plains and minor quartzite plateaus. Bounded by latitudes 12.591672°S and 14.301195°S, and longitudes 130.807472°E and 132.975587°E.

concepts.label: Top End Coastal Plains
concepts.definition: Dissected ferruginous lowlands and minor islands; part alluvial, part estuarine coastal plains. Bounded by latitudes 10.903421°S and 15.936886°S, and longitudes 127.780453°E and 136.984985°E.

concepts.label: Whirlwind Plain
concepts.definition: Alluvial plain, mainly clay. Bounded by latitudes 14.56509°S and 16.421499°S, and longitudes 129.498352°E and 130.92762°E.

concepts.label: North West Cape Ridges
concepts.definition: Low ridges and peninsula formed by folded limestone and sedimentary rocks; sandy plains. Bounded by latitudes 21.78509°S and 23.516084°S, and longitudes 113.627853°E and 114.400577°E.

concepts.label: North West Ramp
concepts.definition: Incised basalt ramp including coastal scarp, with some mudstone and weathered granite. Bounded by latitudes 40.925171°S and 41.55931°S, and longitudes 145.480141°E and 146.594074°E.

concepts.label: Northam Slopes
concepts.definition: Flat-floored valleys of moderately incised oceanward drainage; older ferruginous remnants with breakaways on divides in east; stripped granite on valley sides in west. Bounded by latitudes 30.27922°S and 34.302188°S, and longitudes 115.978955°E and 117.780392°E.

concepts.label: Nullagine Hills
concepts.definition: Dissected flat-topped hills of granitic, volcanic, and metamorphic rocks; interspersed by stony plains on granite. Bounded by latitudes 20.521125°S and 23.593862°S, and longitudes 116.080864°E and 121.413178°E.

concepts.label: Nullarbor Plain Province
concepts.definition: Plateaus, hills and ridges on resistant rocks, with some valley floors. Bounded by latitudes 28.892723°S and 34.108841°S, and longitudes 123.316086°E and 132.708298°E.

concepts.label: Roe Plain
concepts.definition: Coastal limestone plain with extensive dunes. Bounded by latitudes 31.675752°S and 32.321461°S, and longitudes 125.893166°E and 128.995019°E.

concepts.label: Onslow Plain
concepts.definition: Alluvial, deltaic, and littoral plains; some sandplain and coastal dunes; minor islands. Bounded by latitudes 20.35881°S and 22.594877°S, and longitudes 114.303879°E and 116.146432°E.

concepts.label: Palmerville Hills
concepts.definition: Granitic hills and plateaus and sandstone mesas with intervening plains. Bounded by latitudes 15.588526°S and 16.518965°S, and longitudes 143.465556°E and 144.127454°E.

concepts.label: Torres High Islands
concepts.definition: Islands and low coastal tablelands of volcanic rocks and granite, with fringing reefs. Bounded by latitudes 9.35406°S and 10.99771°S, and longitudes 141.909393°E and 142.707413°E.

concepts.label: Wenlock Uplands
concepts.definition: Complex of tablelands and low plateaus with north–south lowlands, including the Great Escarpment, and coastal hills in the east. Bounded by latitudes 12.34867°S and 14.030618°S, and longitudes 142.810422°E and 143.598434°E.

concepts.label: Pilbara Province
concepts.definition: Coastal and alluvial plains, plateaus, scarps, and low hills. Bounded by latitudes 20.014311°S and 27.020391°S, and longitudes 114.943213°E and 123.619433°E.

concepts.label: Redvers Dunefield
concepts.definition: East–west longitudinal dunes. Bounded by latitudes 22.159016°S and 23.233663°S, and longitudes 127.599033°E and 131.672497°E.

concepts.label: Rudall Tablelands
concepts.definition: Dissected low sandstone tablelands with hills and ranges on gneiss and intervening areas of sandplains. Bounded by latitudes 21.424074°S and 23.726928°S, and longitudes 121.341582°E and 123.566975°E.

concepts.label: Salmon Gums Plain
concepts.definition: Flat to undulating plain with salt lakes and occasional granitic low hills. Bounded by latitudes 32.246049°S and 33.6694°S, and longitudes 120.450452°E and 123.671862°E.

concepts.label: Sandland Province
concepts.definition: Higher uplands falling to the east coast. Bounded by latitudes 17.842708°S and 32.196006°S, and longitudes 118.807411°E and 135.621357°E.

concepts.label: Stansmore Dunefield and Ranges
concepts.definition: East–west longitudinal dunes locally broken by narrow sandstone ranges. Bounded by latitudes 19.052684°S and 22.215138°S, and longitudes 125.851631°E and 128.367324°E.

concepts.label: Sturt Creek Floodout
concepts.definition: Floodout with distributary channels and claypan. Bounded by latitudes 19.560462°S and 20.325222°S, and longitudes 127.028081°E and 127.706658°E.

concepts.label: Shark Bay Peninsulas
concepts.definition: Peninsulas, islands, and hinterland formed on indurated limestone dunes; sandplain, dunes and calcrete plains. Bounded by latitudes 25.480511°S and 26.954729°S, and longitudes 112.921501°E and 114.781437°E.

concepts.label: Southern Goldfields Plateau
concepts.definition: Undulating plains with some sandplains, ferruginous breakaways; ridges of metamorphic rocks and granitic hills and rises; calcretes, large salt lakes and dunes along valleys. Bounded by latitudes 29.016662°S and 32.662586°S, and longitudes 117.411349°E and 124.341387°E.

concepts.label: Swan Plain
concepts.definition: Dune ridges (on limestone along the coast) and inner alluvial plain. Bounded by latitudes 30.117897°S and 33.79439°S, and longitudes 114.970154°E and 116.059826°E.

concepts.label: West Tasmanian Ridges
concepts.definition: Ridges of folded quartzite and conglomerate, glaciated in places, parallel valleys on weaker rocks. Bounded by latitudes 40.71249°S and 43.742649°S, and longitudes 144.911068°E and 146.760988°E.

concepts.label: Warren–Denmark Slopes
concepts.definition: Ferruginous plateau, increasingly dissected in the south, exposing on granite and gneiss; finally merging into narrow swampy plain and coastal dunes. Bounded by latitudes 33.878074°S and 35.13485°S, and longitudes 115.748125°E and 17.768831°E.

concepts.label: Western Coastlands Province
concepts.definition: Hills and plains, alluvial plains, some dunes and lakes. Bounded by latitudes 20.3588104855°S and 34.5421327617°S, and longitudes 112.921501077°E and 116.152210277°E.

concepts.label: Yanrey–Cane Plains
concepts.definition: Sandplain and south–north longitudinal dunes with intervening alluvial plains. Bounded by latitudes 21.025096°S and 23.364644°S, and longitudes 114.285043°E and 116.138486°E.

concepts.label: Yaringa Sandplain
concepts.definition: Sandplain with minor dunes; some stony plains. Bounded by latitudes 22.986782°S and 28.419387°S, and longitudes 113.77167°E and 116.15221°E.

concepts.label: Western Plateau Division
concepts.definition: Mosaic of shield blocks and intracratonic basins; plains, plateaus, ranges, dune fields. Bounded by latitudes 10.9034°S and 36.396648°S, and longitudes 112.921501°E and 142.138110°E.

concepts.label: Yilgarn Plateau Province
concepts.definition: This province is more-or-less coincident with the Murray sedimentary basin, consisting of flat alluvium with Eolian cover in places. Bounded by latitudes 25.167211°S and 35.193981 °S, and longitudes 115.212771°E and 124.341387°E.

concepts.label: Woodramung Hills
concepts.definition: Low rounded ridges of folded metamorphics with intervening sandy plains and hardpan wash plains. Bounded by latitudes 27.812263°S and 30.025157°S, and longitudes 115.428416°E and 117.713387°E.
